    "department": "Enterprise Technology",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\nSnowflake is about empowering enterprises to achieve their full potential — and people too. With a culture that’s all in on impact, innovation, and collaboration, Snowflake is the sweet spot for building big, moving fast, and taking technology — and careers — to the next level.\n\nWe are looking for a proactive, hands-on Payroll Product Manager to drive leading-edge solutions within our Workday Payroll and Global Payroll ecosystem. This role is designed for a problem-solver who combines deep U.S. payroll expertise with the technical rigor to transform complex requirements into scalable, compliant system solutions.\n\nYou will work closely with Payroll Operations teams to ensure our payroll systems are automated, resilient, and built for global growth. As a key member, you are expected to bring a “can-do” mindset — willing to pivot as business needs evolve and ready to support the broader organization when complexity arises.\n\n\nKEY RESPONSIBILITIES:\n\nTechnical Delivery \u0026 Configuration: Analyze complex payroll challenges and design automated, scalable solutions. Own hands-on configuration of Workday Payroll, including earnings, deductions, garnishments, tax setup, costing allocations, pay slips, and security frameworks.\n\nPayroll Compliance \u0026 Global Expansion: Ensure multi-state U.S. payroll compliance while supporting global payroll harmonization and country rollouts. Design solutions that balance regulatory rigor with operational efficiency.\n\nIntegrations \u0026 Automation: Design or troubleshoot integrations using Workday EIB, Core Connectors, Studio, and APIs (REST/SOAP). Enable seamless data flow across Payroll, Time Tracking, Benefits, Finance, and third-party vendors.\n\nData-Driven Optimization: Develop or support Workday custom reports (Advanced, Matrix, Composite), Dashboards and Analytics to drive efficiency and controls. Nice to have SQL proficiency and experience with Snowflake.\n\nSDLC Excellence: Lead unit, integration, regression, and UAT testing. Maintain high-quality documentation to ensure payroll configurations and integrations are scalable, secure, and audit-ready.\n\nOperational Governance: Serve as Payroll Systems SME. Support SOX compliance, audit readiness, release impact analysis, and continuous system optimization.\n\nAI Innovation: Develop and execute roadmaps for leveraging AI to streamline payroll processes\n\n\nKNOWLEDGE \u0026 EXPERIENCE REQUIRED:\n\nExperience: 5+ years in a hands-on role focused on Payroll Systems\n\nWorkday Payroll Administration (Must Have): Proven hands-on experience configuring and supporting Workday Payroll.\n\nWorkday Reporting \u0026 Integrations: Experience building Workday Custom Reports and calculated fields. Experience supporting integrations (EIB, Core Connectors, Studio) and working knowledge of Workday APIs (REST/SOAP).\n\nSystems \u0026 Analytical Depth: Strong problem-solving capabilities and the ability to translate complex business requirements into scalable technical solutions.\n\nPayroll Domain Expertise: Strong functional knowledge of U.S. payroll (federal, state, and local compliance).\n\n\nCORE COMPETENCIES:\n\nLow Ego, High Impact: A team-first collaborator who jumps in to support colleagues and stakeholders whenever challenges arise. You don’t complain when asked to help; you see it as an opportunity to drive impact.\n\nArchitectural Thinking: Ability to understand how payroll data flows across HR, Finance, and external vendor ecosystems — designing systems that are scalable, compliant, and future-ready.\n\nProactive Ownership: Self-driven and solutions-oriented. You don’t wait for perfect requirements — you help define them and move execution forward.\n\nCuriosity \u0026 Agility: You naturally question how payroll systems can be smarter, faster, and more automated. You remain effective in ambiguity, adapt quickly in high-growth environments, and continuously look for opportunities to elevate the payroll technology landscape.\n\nEvery Snowflake employee is expected to follow the company’s confidentiality and security standards for handling sensitive data. Snowflake employees must abide by the company’s data security plan as an essential part of their duties. It is every employee's duty to keep customer information secure and confidential.\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
